<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><base target="_self"/><meta charSet="utf-8"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=Edge"/><meta name="google" content="notranslate"/><title data-rh="true">What US Employers Need to Know About AI Hiring Bias Laws in the EU and UK | Fisher Phillips LLP</title><meta name="description" content="Regulators in the European Union (EU) and the United Kingdom (UK) are sharpening their focus on algorithmic discrimination in employment decisions, combining new AI specific rules with established data protection and anti discrimination frameworks. This Insight highlights the key developments you should have on your radar and provides four practical steps you can put into place right away." data-rh="true"/><meta name="keywords" content="AI and employment law, AI employment law, AI in recruiting laws, AI, artificial intelligence, artificial intelligence employment law, AI laws, AI lawsuits, AI news, latest AI news, employment law news, labor and employment law news, law employment news, employment law news today, workplace law blog, employment law blog, labor and employment law blog, employment law articles, labor law articles, labor law news, labor law updates, employment law news, labor and employment law news, law employment news, employment law news today, workplace law blog, employment law blog, labor and employment law blog, employment law articles, labor law articles, labor law news, labor law updates," data-rh="true"/><link rel="canonical" href="https://www.fisherphillips.com/en/insights/insights/what-us-employers-need-to-know-about-ai-hiring-bias-laws-in-the-eu-and-uk"/><link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/build/apple-touch-icon_a503a8d8.png"/><link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="96x96" href="/images/build/favicon-96x96_4949b69c.png"/><link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/images/build/favicon_03998ed0.svg"/><link rel="manife